Encapsulation :- 
Encapsulation is one of the java concept that make any sensitive information private so that it should 
not be accessible to everyone. or 
making sensitive info of the class as private to restrict its direct access. but giving the indirect access.
but giving the direct access by using getter and setter method is called as Encapsulation.


1.making sensitive info of the class as private
2.getter & setter method should be public.
3.private string password;
4.setter method is use to set the value and getter method is use to fetch the value.